<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Marc Tudurí</title><link>https://marctuduri.com/posts/</link><description>Recent content on Marc Tudurí</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Mon, 14 Oct 2024 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://marctuduri.com/posts/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>New template for the site</title><link>https://marctuduri.com/posts/new-template/</link><pubDate>Mon, 14 Oct 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://marctuduri.com/posts/new-template/</guid><description>&lt;p>For a long time I wanted to update my bio, I joined Grafana 2 years ago and I didn&amp;rsquo;t update yet&amp;hellip;&lt;em>Good Ol&amp;rsquo; Obsolescence&lt;/em> made the current version of Hugo be incompatible with the previous theme, so I had to update it.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>This time I used &lt;a href="https://github.com/jpanther/congo" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">congo&lt;/a> which has some nice features like dark mode. I also added a GitHub action to deploy the site to GitHub pages. Before I had two different repos, one for the source code and another for the generated site.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>How to use Grafana Beyla in Grafana Alloy for eBPF-based auto-instrumentation</title><link>https://marctuduri.com/posts/beyla-alloy/</link><pubDate>Tue, 21 May 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://marctuduri.com/posts/beyla-alloy/</guid><description>&lt;p>Posted in &lt;a href="https://grafana.com/blog/2024/05/21/how-to-use-grafana-beyla-in-grafana-alloy-for-ebpf-based-auto-instrumentation/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Grafana Labs blog&lt;/a>.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>What Is New with Periskop in 2022</title><link>https://marctuduri.com/posts/periskop/</link><pubDate>Tue, 01 Feb 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://marctuduri.com/posts/periskop/</guid><description>&lt;p>Posted in &lt;a href="https://developers.soundcloud.com/blog/periskop-in-2022" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">SoundCloud Backstage blog&lt;/a>.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Service Architecture - Domain Gateways</title><link>https://marctuduri.com/posts/domain-gateways/</link><pubDate>Fri, 17 Sep 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://marctuduri.com/posts/domain-gateways/</guid><description>&lt;p>Posted in &lt;a href="https://developers.soundcloud.com/blog/service-architecture-3" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">SoundCloud Backstage blog&lt;/a>.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Service Architecture - Value-Added Services</title><link>https://marctuduri.com/posts/vas/</link><pubDate>Fri, 20 Aug 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://marctuduri.com/posts/vas/</guid><description>&lt;p>Posted in &lt;a href="https://developers.soundcloud.com/blog/service-architecture-2" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">SoundCloud Backstage blog&lt;/a>.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Using Prometheus for monitoring Django applications in Kubernetes</title><link>https://marctuduri.com/posts/prometheus-kubernetes-django/</link><pubDate>Mon, 08 Oct 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://marctuduri.com/posts/prometheus-kubernetes-django/</guid><description>&lt;h3 id="django-application-deployment-architecture" class="relative group">Django application deployment architecture &lt;span class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100">&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700" style="text-decoration-line: none !important;" href="#django-application-deployment-architecture" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>&lt;/span>&lt;/h3>&lt;p>Developing web applications with &lt;a href="https://www.djangoproject.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Django&lt;/a> is very easy and fun: if you just follow the &lt;a href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/2.1/intro/tutorial01/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">tutorial&lt;/a> in a few hours you can have up and running your own website. However, deploying a Django site can be hard and you can end up running a site with a terrible performance if you don&amp;rsquo;t follow the recommended guidelines to deploy a Django site to a production environment.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>New site with Hugo</title><link>https://marctuduri.com/posts/new-site/</link><pubDate>Sun, 01 Jul 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://marctuduri.com/posts/new-site/</guid><description>&lt;p>Hi,&lt;/p>
&lt;p>My old site was a little bit abandoned and hard to update so I decided to renew it.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>For this time, I decided to use a static site generator so I gave a chance to &lt;a href="https://gohugo.io" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Hugo&lt;/a>. I never tried before but I discovered that it has its own &lt;a href="https://themes.gohugo.io/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">themes site&lt;/a> which is awesome as saves you a lot of customization time. By the way, if you wonder what template I&amp;rsquo;m using is the &lt;a href="https://themes.gohugo.io/cocoa-eh-hugo-theme/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Cocoa enhanced theme&lt;/a>.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>